Since the age of 15, Clarke had been playing in their second team as a No 5 batsman, while making occasional outings for the firsts as a left-arm tweaker who batted No 8. One hundred against Sutherland at Caringbah Oval - formerly Glenn McGrath’s hunting ground - caught the eye of ‘Jungle Jim’ Robson, a New South Wales state selector whose son, Sam, is now opening the batting for Middlesex.
